    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-11-04T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-11-04T14:00:00-05:00" n="486"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d486">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.30/214: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-11-04T16:00:00-03:00"
                            >November 4, 1930—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 4:11 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>140. Mello Franco, Foreign Minister of the Provisional Government,<note n="22"
                        xml:id="d486fn22">See “Revolution in Brazil,” <ref target="#pg_432">pp.
                            432</ref> ff.</note> sent his Chief of Cabinet to the Embassy today to
                    state that as the Provisional Government had not had sufficient opportunity to
                    decide whether or not they wish to renew the Naval Mission contract, they desire
                    that the Mission would continue to operate after the termination of the present
                    contract on November 6th until the Government had an opportunity to reach a
                    decision probably within 15 days.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Morgan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
